  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Planning & Scheduling Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job description:</strong><br /><br /><strong>Project Scheduling：</strong><br />• Develop and maintain detailed project schedules using project management software (e.g., Primavera P6, Microsoft Project).<br />• Establish baseline schedules and monitor progress against these benchmarks.</p><p><strong>Resource Management:</strong><br />• Coordinate with project managers to determine resource requirements and ensure optimal allocation.<br />• Analyze resource usage and make recommendations for adjustments to meet project goals.</p><p><strong>Progress Monitoring:</strong><br />• Track project progress and report on key milestones, delays, and resource utilization.<br />• Conduct regular site visits to gather data and assess the progress of construction activities.</p><p><strong>Risk Management:</strong><br />• Identify potential risks and delays in the project timeline, proposing solutions and mitigation strategies.<br />• Conduct impact analysis for changes in project scope or schedule, ensuring timely communication with stakeholders</p><p><strong>Reporting and Documentation:</strong><br />• Prepare and present progress reports, schedules, and forecasts to project management and stakeholders.<br />• Maintain documentation of schedule changes, delays, and mitigation measures taken</p><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years of relevant planning and scheduling experience in the construction industry, preferably with a main contractor.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>Primavera P6</strong> and <strong>Microsoft Project</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of construction methods, sequencing, and project lifecycle.</p></li><li><p>Experience with high-rise buildings, infrastructure, or large-scale civil projects is advantageous.</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Singapore construction regulations and safety requirements is preferred.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Preferred Attributes:</strong></h2><p><p>PMP, PSP, or equivalent professional certification is an advantage.</p></p><p>Ability to work independently and manage multiple project schedules simultaneously.\n\n</p>",
